{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SDQtrRfJ4qyEMYctTSKPF4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The test reads a file and parses it with UCL. The failing test is with `11.in` which contains `{\"key\": \"value\"}`. This is a JSON file. The expected output in `11.res` is `key = \"value\";` which is UCL format.\n\nThe exit code is 254 (which would be -2 in signed int, or `exit(-errno)` where errno=2=ENOENT).\n\nWait, exit code 254 = -2 as signed... Actually:\n- `exit(-errno)` where errno=2 (ENOENT - file not found)\n- -2 in uint8 = 254\n\n\nSo the test is failing because it can't find the input file. The test invokes the binary with a relative path `../tests/basic/11.in` from the `/work` directory, which would resolve to `/tests/basic/11.in` — but that file doesn't exist. The path resolution is off. I'm realizing the path issue depends on where the test is executed from—if run from `/work/tests/`, then `../tests/basic/11.in` resolves to `/work/tests/basic/11.in` which exists, but running from `/work` would look for `/tests/basic/11.in` which doesn't. The exit code 254 (which is -2 in signed form) matches errno 2 (ENOENT), so the file open is failing because the path is wrong relative to the working directory.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2044,"cache_read_input_tokens":23036,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2044},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"738e3405-02e2-43f7-b396-8141f9d90a30","uuid":"ad6d4bd4-4b8d-4b9b-a030-b04fc4b1918a"}
